author: Staff Writer - Unlimited Digital Access
title: Instant Analysis: LSU women's basketball takes down Ole Miss to win first SEC road game
text: Instant Analysis: LSU women's basketball takes down Ole Miss to win first SEC road game LSU's winning streak continued on the road against an SEC opponent on Sunday. The Tigers took down Ole Miss in Oxford 84-73 to win their 15th game in a row and begin conference play with a 2-0 record. The first quarter was tight with LSU leading by just three after 10 minutes. But as has been the case most of this year, it controlled the second quarter, outscoring the Rebels 24-14 to take a 50-37 lead going into the locker room. It looked like LSU was once again ready to pull away, but the third quarter was a different story. The Tigers shot just 30% as Ole Miss got back into the game, cutting the lead to 67-62 entering the fourth. Ultimately, though, LSU weathered the storm while shooting 50% in the final frame. Angel Reese nearly had a double-double with 21 points and nine rebounds, while freshman Mikaylah Williams scored 20 points. They were two of five Tigers who scored in double figures. LSU struggled to defend Ole Miss forward Marquesha Davis, who had 24 points, but it was an overall sound defensive performance. The Tigers will now have a few days off as they prepare to host [Texas A&M](http://aggieswire.usatoday.com) on Thursday night. title: Meta Platforms (META) to Release New Standalone AI App
text:
Meta Platforms (META) has announced that it plans to release a standalone artificial intelligence (AI) app as it moves to compete more directly against OpenAIâ€™s ChatGPT.
CNBC is reporting that Meta Platforms plans to launch an AI app similar to its family of social media apps that includes Facebook, Instagram and WhatsApp. The Silicon Valley-based company intends to debut its new â€œMeta AIâ€ app in this yearâ€™s second quarter.
The AI app is seen as a shot across the bow of privately held OpenAI, whose ChatGPT chatbot is widely viewed as the leading AI app within the U.S. The new AI app also comes as Meta CEO Mark Zuckerberg plans to make his company the leader in AI by the end of this year, moving ahead of competitors such as OpenAI, Microsoft (MSFT), Alphabet (GOOGL), and others.
AI Initiatives
Metaâ€™s new standalone AI app follows the launch of the companyâ€™s Meta AI chatbot in September 2023, marketing it as a generative AI-powered digital assistant that can provide responses and create images based on user prompts. Meta has also integrated AI into some features found on Facebook, Instagram, WhatsApp and Messenger.
However, this would be the companyâ€™s first standalone AI app available for download and use on smartphones similar to ChatGPT and the Chinese app DeepSeek. Meta Platforms also reportedly has plans for a paid subscription service, similar to how OpenAI charges users monthly fees for users to access its ChatGPT app.
META stock has risen 39% over the last 12 months.
Is META Stock a Buy?
The stock of Meta Platforms has a consensus Strong Buy rating among 48 Wall Street analysts. That rating is based on 44 Buy, three Hold, and one Sell recommendations issued in the past three months. The average META price target of $764.61 implies 14.17% upside from current levels.

At the center of the bad weather there is once again the Island of the Knights which is still measuring its wounds from the bad weather Bora

In Rhodes 112 rang again by the Civil Protection and while the Isola dei Cavalieri is still feeling the wounds of the Bora bad weather.
According to 112, residents are invited to limit travel within municipal communities Ialyssou, Rhodes, Kallithea and Petaloudon.
The first severe storm occurred at 3am on Friday in the city of Rhodes and other areas of it northern triangle of the island fortunately without causing serious problems.
It should be noted that EMY provides continuity heavy rain and thunderstorms for the entire Dodecanese from today Friday (6/12) until and, at least, Sunday morning hours (8/12).
The 112 also played in Psara with the Civil Protection inviting residents to limit movements as heavy rain and thunderstorms are forecast for the next 24 hours.
